Always-Less-Effort method

Method and relative algorithm to obtain a workload schedule in a linear-descending manner, utilizing user-defined parameters to establish the ratio between the workload at the beginning and at the end of the process.
This method ensures compliance with the constraint of completing the entire workload within pre-established deadlines, while simultaneously allowing users to define a custom increase in initial effort relative to the final days.
Algorithms, use cases, output examples, and mathematical formulations are provided herein.
